{"parse":{"title":"Planning Accreditation Board","pageid":31630283,"revid":814261092,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:PAB_logo_Jun_2007.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"PAB logo Jun 2007.JPG\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/5/5f/PAB_logo_Jun_2007.JPG/220px-PAB_logo_Jun_2007.JPG\" width=\"220\" height=\"330\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/5/5f/PAB_logo_Jun_2007.JPG 1.5x\" data-file-width=\"258\" data-file-height=\"387\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:PAB_logo_Jun_2007.JPG\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div></div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>Planning Accreditation Board</b> (PAB) is a non-profit professional accreditation agency jointly sponsored by the Association of Collegiate Schools of Planning (ACSP), the <a href=\"/wiki/American_Planning_Association\" title=\"American Planning Association\">American Planning Association</a> (APA) and the APA\u2019s professional institute the <a href=\"/wiki/American_Institute_of_Certified_Planners\" title=\"American Institute of Certified Planners\">American Institute of Certified Planners</a> (AICP). The Planning Accreditation Board\u2019s mission is to ensure high quality education for future <a href=\"/wiki/Urban_planners\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Urban planners\">urban planners</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>PAB accredits graduate and undergraduate planning degree programs in the United States and Canada. As of January 1, 2016, there are 86 planning programs (15 Bachelors and 71 Masters programs) in 75 North American Universities accredited by PAB.\n</p><p>All PAB-accredited programs must meet the <i>PAB Accreditation Standards and Criteria</i> found on the PAB website. The policies and procedures governing accreditation are available in PAB's <i>Policies and Procedures Manual.</i> \n</p><p>PAB was founded in 1984, as it was deemed necessary to assess quality and encourage excellence in higher education. Prior to this formal accreditation process, there was a recognition program in place administered by the National Education Development Committee (NEDC) of the American Institute of Planners (AIP).<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>PAB is recognized by the <a href=\"/wiki/Council_on_Higher_Education_Accreditation\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Council on Higher Education Accreditation\">Council on Higher Education Accreditation</a> and is a member of the Association of Professional and Specialized Accreditors.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The national office of the Planning Accreditation Board is located in Chicago, IL.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Planning_Accreditation_Board&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.planningaccreditationboard.org\">Planning Accreditation Board Official Website</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.aspa-usa.org/\">Association of Professional and Specialized Accreditors</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.acsp.org/\">Association of Collegiate Schools of Planning</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Planning_Accreditation_Board&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.planningaccreditationboard.org\">Planning Accreditation Board</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.planningaccreditationboard.org\">Planning Accreditation Board, <i>History of Accreditation in Planning Education</i></a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.planningaccreditationboard.org\">Planning Accreditation Board</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw2271\nCached time: 20180917221107\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.016 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.021 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 44/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 0/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 1145/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    0.000      1 -total\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:31630283-0!canonical and timestamp 20180917221107 and revision id 814261092\n -->\n</div>"},"langlinks":[],"categories":[{"sortkey":"","*":"School_accreditors"}],"links":[{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"American Institute of Certified Planners"},{"n